sue issue.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.062554,0.11491,0.131,0.11777,0.10412,0.087652,0.080721,0.071946,0.065097,0.064643,0.051985,0.047606],"unified_progress":[0.050621,0.08609,0.095073,0.10813,0.1026,0.09663,0.094116,0.087335,0.0824,0.080839,0.064826,0.051347]},{"section":9,"text":"The key here is the click and the location.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048636,0.099025,0.12179,0.1212,0.10576,0.088303,0.081231,0.073855,0.068497,0.074103,0.059867,0.057728],"unified_progress":[0.041947,0.074723,0.08754,0.1006,0.098738,0.094145,0.097211,0.091621,0.087713,0.091756,0.074845,0.059157]},{"section":10,"text":"The click when compressing the forefoot and pressing on the interdigital space...","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.057124,0.10246,0.10321,0.10224,0.096792,0.09438,0.088311,0.08257,0.080418,0.070563,0.063037,0.058889],"unified_progress":[0.058334,0.081162,0.090805,0.10695,0.10036,0.097117,0.093672,0.089641,0.08643,0.074374,0.063966,0.057194]},{"section":11,"text":"I remember that Morton's neuroma is a common cause of metatarsalgia.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04448,0.080375,0.091991,0.10078,0.10356,0.099586,0.098125,0.090079,0.081294,0.081207,0.066377,0.062153],"unified_progress":[0.049672,0.063777,0.08473,0.093885,0.09708,0.11356,0.10081,0.095599,0.089179,0.085112,0.0696,0.056996]},{"section":12,"text":"It typically occurs between the third and fourth toes.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043251,0.080117,0.086777,0.093992,0.098534,0.10011,0.098899,0.093275,0.086914,0.083737,0.070305,0.064093],"unified_progress":[0.051376,0.067906,0.083943,0.09364,0.097979,0.10303,0.09973,0.097179,0.092032,0.083763,0.070212,0.059206]},{"section":13,"text":"The classic signs are tenderness between the metatarsal heads, and sometimes a click (called a Mulder's click) which is a palpable or audible click when the neuroma is squeezed.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047277,0.08588,0.088724,0.092836,0.095441,0.097413,0.096291,0.092059,0.087395,0.081844,0.069748,0.065091],"unified_progress":[0.052249,0.07211,0.086211,0.093771,0.097932,0.1027,0.098,0.095635,0.091611,0.082022,0.069408,0.058346]},{"section":14,"text":"Morton's neuroma is a benign thickening of the nerve, usually the interdigital nerve, often between the 3rd and 4th metatarsals.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046964,0.080786,0.085866,0.093315,0.097254,0.09827,0.09763,0.091874,0.087046,0.083304,0.070056,0.067634],"unified_progress":[0.056338,0.065041,0.083249,0.092446,0.097217,0.10479,0.099174,0.095882,0.091827,0.082419,0.070438,0.061177]},{"section":15,"text":"It's more common in women, especially those in narrow shoes or with high-impact activities like running.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03775,0.074264,0.082394,0.089763,0.097004,0.10462,0.10096,0.097876,0.090671,0.088313,0.07542,0.06096],"unified_progress":[0.082767,0.095018,0.090643,0.087885,0.089203,0.094445,0.089211,0.09248,0.083419,0.078013,0.065433,0.051485]},{"section":16,"text":"The pain is often described as burning or aching, and it can feel like there's a pebble in the shoe.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04855,0.086813,0.085968,0.087275,0.091061,0.095466,0.095721,0.096998,0.089363,0.083878,0.074517,0.06439],"unified_progress":[0.070303,0.084052,0.089766,0.090335,0.091936,0.095834,0.091353,0.093251,0.086859,0.081463,0.069386,0.055462]},{"section":17,"text":"The exam finding of the click when compressing the area is a big clue here.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041375,0.080369,0.089686,0.092844,0.092444,0.091847,0.092017,0.089531,0.090103,0.086438,0.07846,0.074886],"unified_progress":[0.048726,0.073136,0.083833,0.092206,0.095642,0.095709,0.094404,0.09216,0.092006,0.086572,0.077602,0.068004]},{"section":18,"text":"Other possibilities might include stress fracture, but that usually has more localized tenderness and might show up on X-ray, which the case doesn't mention.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023367,0.057168,0.072915,0.083111,0.089853,0.094693,0.10337,0.10531,0.10481,0.10187,0.094339,0.06919],"unified_progress":[0.02754,0.057373,0.073165,0.082221,0.094695,0.095907,0.10094,0.10625,0.10558,0.10975,0.088929,0.057651]},{"section":19,"text":"Also, a plantar wart or bursitis could be considered, but the click is more specific.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020768,0.053303,0.069369,0.080323,0.088047,0.094416,0.10346,0.10721,0.10806,0.10599,0.097236,0.071817],"unified_progress":[0.025283,0.055382,0.072141,0.082856,0.093035,0.097127,0.10296,0.10779,0.10796,0.11061,0.089159,0.055695]},{"section":20,"text":"Maybe a ganglion cyst, but again, the location and the click point more towards neuroma.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023058,0.054736,0.069737,0.080001,0.087008,0.09263,0.10037,0.1036,0.10633,0.10422,0.097279,0.081026],"unified_progress":[0.028722,0.05459,0.070914,0.082218,0.091459,0.095323,0.10062,0.10451,0.10565,0.10678,0.091252,0.067964]},{"section":21,"text":"So putting it all together: active female, pain between 3rd and 4th toes, Mulder's click on exam.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035241,0.066307,0.072848,0.078452,0.083514,0.088557,0.091788,0.09363,0.097589,0.096943,0.096357,0.098775],"unified_progress":[0.043045,0.057636,0.067754,0.077151,0.084279,0.091204,0.09375,0.096455,0.099453,0.09791,0.098009,0.093353]},{"section":22,"text":"Most likely Morton's neuroma.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02351,0.048175,0.059625,0.067232,0.073483,0.078223,0.084945,0.088699,0.096219,0.10176,0.11235,0.16578],"unified_progress":[0.02252,0.036172,0.046132,0.055927,0.061327,0.073322,0.077761,0.089905,0.1011,0.10935,0.14172,0.18476]}]}}